Cotton for December delivery on ICE
Futures U.S. in New York advanced for a fifth day, reversing an
earlier decline.  The contract rose as much as 1.2 percent to $1.372 a pound
and traded at $1.3692 at 11:05 a.m. in Singapore.  To contact the reporter on this story:
